Here is a chronology of events that began

2 a.m. _ The main body of troops is stopped several hundred yards east of the vast square by thousands of people.
2 p.m. _ About 5,000 troops emerge from Great Hall of the People on the western side of the square and are surrounded by crowds.
1 a.m. Sunday.
More people shot as troops fire at crowds.
2 a.m. _ Thousands of troops arrive at the west side of the square and some of the riflemen open fire.
4:30 a.m. _ Armored personnel carriers enter the square.
